  "response_text": "# Healthy Chicken Breast Seasoning\n\nHere are some great options:\n\n**Simple & Classic**\n- Lemon juice, garlic, and fresh herbs (rosemary, thyme, or oregano)\n- Salt, pepper, and a touch of olive oil\n\n**Flavorful Blends**\n- Paprika, cumin, and garlic powder (smoky flavor)\n- Italian seasoning with balsamic vinegar\n- Ginger, garlic, and low-sodium soy sauce (Asian-inspired)\n\n**Fresh Herb Approach**\n- Cilantro, lime juice, and cumin\n- Fresh basil, lemon zest, and black pepper\n\n**Tips for Maximum Flavor**\n- Use fresh herbs when possible—they're more flavorful than dried\n- Add acid (lemon, lime, vinegar) to enhance taste without salt\n- Let seasoning sit 15-30 minutes before cooking\n- Skip salt or use it sparingly; herbs provide plenty of flavor\n\nThese methods add taste without excess sodium, sugar, or unhealthy fats—keeping your meal both delicious and nutritious.",
